<subSubSection pageId="28" pageNumber="317" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="28.[151,760,875,1891]" pageId="28" pageNumber="317">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,268,875,899]" pageId="28" pageNumber="317">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Antennae reddish. Antennomere II longer than III. Pronotum with smoky stripe reaching posterior margin. Thoracic and abdominal pleurites and sternites with black spots (
<figureCitation box="[286,369,972,995]" captionStart="Figs 5" captionStartId="6.[151,188,2034,2053]" captionTargetBox="[248,1334,197,1986]" captionTargetId="figure-13@6.[179,1408,189,1996]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figs 5A–F.Dorsal and ventral surface.A–B – Hypoxys servillei sp. nov.; C–D – Hypoxys stysi sp. nov.; E–F – Hypoxys venustus sp. nov. Scale bars = 5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177537" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177537/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="317">Fig. 5F</figureCitation>
). Anterior excavation of metasternal process harboring fourth and third rostral segment (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figs 20" captionStartId="26.[151,188,2038,2057]" captionTargetBox="[200,1411,202,1977]" captionTargetId="figure-13@26.[177,1411,189,2003]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="Figs 20A–E. Hypoxys venustus sp. nov. A–D – pygophore in dorsal, ventral, posterior and posterolateral view, respectively; E – metasternal process. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177565" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177565/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="317">Fig. 20E</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[216,381,1035,1059]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="317">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Pygophore (
<figureCitation box="[517,654,1036,1059]" captionStart="Figs 20" captionStartId="26.[151,188,2038,2057]" captionTargetBox="[200,1411,202,1977]" captionTargetId="figure-13@26.[177,1411,189,2003]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="Figs 20A–E. Hypoxys venustus sp. nov. A–D – pygophore in dorsal, ventral, posterior and posterolateral view, respectively; E – metasternal process. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177565" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177565/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="317">Figs 20A–D</figureCitation>
). Posterolateral angles developed, straight, rounded (
<figureCitation box="[615,712,1068,1091]" captionStart="Figs 20" captionStartId="26.[151,188,2038,2057]" captionTargetBox="[200,1411,202,1977]" captionTargetId="figure-13@26.[177,1411,189,2003]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="Figs 20A–E. Hypoxys venustus sp. nov. A–D – pygophore in dorsal, ventral, posterior and posterolateral view, respectively; E – metasternal process. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177565" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177565/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="317">Fig. 20A</figureCitation>
) not reaching level of projections of ventral rim (
<figureCitation box="[647,748,1100,1123]" captionStart="Figs 20" captionStartId="26.[151,188,2038,2057]" captionTargetBox="[200,1411,202,1977]" captionTargetId="figure-13@26.[177,1411,189,2003]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="Figs 20A–E. Hypoxys venustus sp. nov. A–D – pygophore in dorsal, ventral, posterior and posterolateral view, respectively; E – metasternal process. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177565" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177565/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="317">Fig. 20B</figureCitation>
). Superior process of genital cup parallel to dorsal rim, long, reaching posterolateral angles, slightly concave medially; inner (proximal) part truncate, ventral angle projected in dentiform process, adjacent to this angle emerges carina almost parallel to this process; outer (distal) part tonguelike (
<figureCitation box="[204,332,1292,1315]" captionStart="Figs 20" captionStartId="26.[151,188,2038,2057]" captionTargetBox="[200,1411,202,1977]" captionTargetId="figure-13@26.[177,1411,189,2003]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="Figs 20A–E. Hypoxys venustus sp. nov. A–D – pygophore in dorsal, ventral, posterior and posterolateral view, respectively; E – metasternal process. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177565" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177565/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="317">Figs 20C,D</figureCitation>
). Paramere with two lobes; anterior lobe triangular, developed, and directed to base of proctiger; lateral and dorsal lobes short and rounded (
<figureCitation box="[619,748,1356,1379]" captionStart="Figs 20" captionStartId="26.[151,188,2038,2057]" captionTargetBox="[200,1411,202,1977]" captionTargetId="figure-13@26.[177,1411,189,2003]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="Figs 20A–E. Hypoxys venustus sp. nov. A–D – pygophore in dorsal, ventral, posterior and posterolateral view, respectively; E – metasternal process. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177565" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177565/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="317">Figs 20C,D</figureCitation>
). Proctiger with tufts of short setae along lateral excavation; posterior face triangular (
<figureCitation box="[429,560,1420,1443]" captionStart="Figs 20" captionStartId="26.[151,188,2038,2057]" captionTargetBox="[200,1411,202,1977]" captionTargetId="figure-13@26.[177,1411,189,2003]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="Figs 20A–E. Hypoxys venustus sp. nov. A–D – pygophore in dorsal, ventral, posterior and posterolateral view, respectively; E – metasternal process. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177565" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177565/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="317">Figs 20C,D</figureCitation>
). Ventral rim with expansion triangular, distally blunt, ventrolateral side with broad striated excavation, dorsal side without brown spot; apices clearly surpassing level of posterolateral angle (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figs 20" captionStartId="26.[151,188,2038,2057]" captionTargetBox="[200,1411,202,1977]" captionTargetId="figure-13@26.[177,1411,189,2003]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="Figs 20A–E. Hypoxys venustus sp. nov. A–D – pygophore in dorsal, ventral, posterior and posterolateral view, respectively; E – metasternal process. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177565" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177565/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="317">Fig. 20B</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[218,410,1547,1571]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="317">Female genitalia.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
